0Cascio%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20emeritus%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Colorado%20Denver%2C%20who's%20researched%20corporate%20cutbacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20wondering%20when%20the%20ax%20is%20going%20to%20fall%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%20That%20pushes%20remaining%20workers%20to%20start%20looking%20around%2C%20especially%20if%20layoffs%20continue%20without%20an%20all%20clear%20from%20the%20company.%20%26quot%3BThey%20spend%20a%20lot%20more%20time%20surfing%20the%20web%2C%20getting%20their%20CVs%20up%20to%20date%2C%20networking%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20detracts%20from%20productivity.%20There's%20no%20way%20around%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECascio%20said%20that%20at%20organizations%20that%20shed%20workers%2C%20the%20share%20who%20leave%20voluntarily%20typically%20goes%20up%20about%2050%25%20in%20the%20following%20year.%20And%20often%2C%20those%20departing%20are%20the%20ones%20who%20are%20%26quot%3Bmost%20marketable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20Tesla%2C%20which%20has%20lost%20several%20high-profile%20execs%20recently.%20One%20of%20the%20most%20recent%2C%20Rich%20Otto%2C%20the%20former%20head%20of%20product%20launches%2C%20said%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20he'd%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-exec-rich-otto-says-resigned-layoffs-hurt-morale-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecided%20to%20resign%3C%2Fa%3E%20amid%20the%20mass%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20recent%20layoffs%20that%20are%20rocking%20the%20company%20and%20its%20morale%20have%20thrown%20this%20harmony%20out%20of%20balance%20and%20it's%20hard%20to%20see%20the%20long-game%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20on%20LinkedIn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-happening-at-tech-firms-that-are-doing-just-fine-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecuts%20at%20tech%20firms%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20coming%20even%20as%20the%20companies%20are%20doing%20well%20overall.%20Yet%20leaders%20can%20feel%20a%20need%20to%20let%20go%20of%20workers%20for%20reasons%20that%20include%20pleasing%20Wall%20Street%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-comments-tech-company-layoffs-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoperating%20more%20efficiently%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20focusing%20on%20newer%20efforts%20like%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20and%20generally%20making%20do%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-new-normal-constant-layoffs-job-cuts-google-amazon-meta-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslower-growth%20environment%3C%2Fa%3E%20brought%20on%2C%20in%20part%2C%20by%20interest%20rates%20that%20are%20far%20higher%20than%20just%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20as%20BI%20has%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20the%20cuts%20don't%20always%20come%20all%20at%20once%20is%20because%20companies%20are%20trying%20to%20address%20changes%20where%20they%20believe%20they%20need%20them%20rather%20than%20making%20across-the-board%20cuts%2C%20Harvard's%20Sucher%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224435cc0d-d1fc-470e-bc32-07f7f1178b43%5C%22%3EIt's%20tough%20to%20recruit%20with%20a%20reputation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20prestigious%20names%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20can%20have%20an%20easier%20time%20making%20routine%20cuts%20because%20they%20have%20a%20steady%20supply%20of%20people%20who'd%20like%20to%20add%20a%20high-profile%20logo%20to%20their%20LinkedIn%20profiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20think%20that%20their%20brand%20is%20bulletproof%2C%26quot%3B%20Cascio%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20big-name%20tech%20companies.%20%26quot%3BTo%20some%20extent%2C%20it%20is%2C%20but%20that's%20not%20true%20of%20most%20employers%20%E2%80%94%20by%20far%20the%20majority%20of%20employers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20for%20the%20biggest%20names%20in%20tech%2C%20there%20can%20still%20be%20harm%20at%20the%20margins%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20recruiting%20top%20talent%2C%20he%20said.%20Those%20who%20might%20entertain%20multiple%20offers%20will%20consider%20where%20there%20have%20been%20cuts%20and%20often%20will%20opt%20for%20the%20company%20that%20has%20never%20had%20layoffs%20rather%20than%20one%20that%20has%20gone%20through%20multiple%20rounds%2C%20Cascio%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20tiebreaker%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Gen%20Zers%20entering%20the%20workforce%20are%20prioritizing%20employment%20security%20%E2%80%94%20knowing%20that%20even%20if%20their%20jobs%20change%20within%20an%20organization%2C%20they%20still%20have%20a%20role%20there%2C%20Cascio%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECaroline%20Ogawa%2C%20a%20director%20in%20the%20HR%20practice%20at%20the%20research%20firm%20Gartner%2C%20said%20that%20even%20though%20the%20job%20market%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-slump-professional-white-collar-jobs-recession-high-salary-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhite-collar%20employees%20might%20be%20softening%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20workers%20have%20yet%20to%20let%20go%20of%20the%20sense%20of%20power%20they%20developed%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20ago%20during%20the%20Great%20Resignation.%20That%20means%20many%20are%20remaining%20picky%20about%20where%20they%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20candidates%20may%20be%20receiving%20fewer%20offers%2C%20their%20expectations%20have%20held%20firm%2C%26quot%3B%20Ogawa%20said.%20%26quot%3BWith%20that%20level%20of%20candidate%20agency%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20hard%20to%20replace%20those%20employees.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2228df1bcb-aaf1-4df7-8382-ad48cc5408b8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDumping%20on%20your%20former%20employer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESocial%20media%20makes%20it%20easier%20for%20spurned%20workers%20to%20sound%20off%20on%20how%20their%20former%20employers%20handled%20a%20layoff%2C%20Cascio%20said.%20That's%20a%20risk%20that%20didn't%20exist%20years%20ago%20and%20one%20that%20even%20top%20companies%20face%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20recruiting%20the%20next%20hot%20job%20prospects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20so%20easy%20to%20tarnish%20a%20company's%20reputation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGartner's%20Ogawa%20also%20told%20BI%20that%20when%20employers%20lay%20off%20workers%2C%20those%20left%20behind%20are%20often%20forced%20to%20take%20on%20the%20work%20once%20done%20by%20their%20former%20colleagues.%20That%20can%20lead%20to%20burnout%20and%20even%20disengagement%2C%20prompting%20some%20to%20wonder%20what%20their%20purpose%20at%20the%20organization%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20makes%20it%20important%20for%20leaders%20to%20communicate%20about%20why%20they're%20making%20the%20reductions%20and%20how%20workers%20can%20re-engage%20with%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFear%20is%20managed%20through%20transparency%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarvard's%20Sucher%20also%20said%20offering%20workers%20a%20rationale%20for%20cuts%20is%20essential%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20for%20those%20who%20are%20getting%20let%20go%20but%20for%20those%20who%20remain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B'What's%20the%20reason%3F'%20And%2C%20'How%20plausible%20is%20the%20reason%3F'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20It%20matters%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20you're%20communicating%20externally%2C%20but%20it%20matters%20hugely%20when%20you're%20communicating%20internally.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-layoffs-could-harm-productivity-recruitment-reputation-tesla-google-microsoft-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715507536000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663e778ab4abc992e8c87427%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-layoffs-could-harm-productiv