't%20always%20know%20she%20would%20be%20relying%20on%20just%20her%20sole%20income%20to%20get%20by.%20Before%20she%20got%20divorced%2019%20years%20ago%2C%20Crystal%20said%20her%20then-husband%20was%20making%20good%20wages%20at%20his%20job%2C%20and%20while%20she%20was%20still%20working%20during%20that%20time%2C%20her%20earnings%20were%20%26quot%3Bsecondary%20income%2C%26quot%3B%20used%20for%20day-to-day%20expenses%20like%20groceries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECrystal's%20concerns%20are%20shared%20widely%20across%20her%20age%20group.%20A%20recent%20survey%20from%20AARP%20found%20that%2C%20among%20Americans%20aged%2050%20and%20above%2C%20one%20in%20five%20of%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-baby-boomers-savings-cant-afford-retirement-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%20having%20no%20retirement%20savings%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20over%20half%20of%20them%20don't%20think%20they'll%20have%20enough%20money%20to%20sustain%20them%20in%20retirement.%20Separately%2C%20a%20report%20from%20the%20Alliance%20for%20Lifetime%20Income's%20Retirement%20Income%20Institute%20found%20that%20over%20half%20of%20a%20cohort%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-retirement-of-peak-boomers-could-affect-economy-social-security-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalled%20%26quot%3Bpeak%20boomers%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20those%20born%20between%201959%20and%201964%2C%20have%20%24250%2C000%20or%20less%20in%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20means%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20them%20will%20primarily%20rely%20on%20Social%20Security%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20program%20is%20projected%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-will-social-security-benefits-run-out-retirement-crisis-boomers-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eno%20longer%20be%20able%20to%20pay%20out%20full%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%202035%20unless%20Congress%20intervenes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECrystal%20said%20that%20with%20all%20of%20her%20daily%20expenses%2C%20her%20finances%20are%20strained%2C%20and%20she%20doesn't%20think%20she'll%20ever%20be%20able%20to%20fully%20retire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20all%20struggling%20with%20food%20and%20utilities.%20Bills%20are%20like%20%2465%20a%20month%20for%20water%2C%20about%20%2480%20to%20%24100%20for%20electricity%20and%20things%20like%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I'm%20one%20of%20these%20people%20that%20walk%20around%20the%20supermarket%20with%20the%20calculator%20on%20my%20phone%20and%20keep%20track%20of%20each%20thing%20as%20I%20put%20it%20in%20the%20cart.%20It's%20a%20tight%20budget.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225332768b-a14b-4e79-a3e8-d3efe5b73219%5C%22%3E'It's%20scary%20out%20there'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20for%20a%20lack%20of%20trying.%20Crystal%20said%20that%20she's%20done%20just%20about%20all%20she%20could%20to%20earn%20more%20income%20%E2%80%94%20she%20sent%20out%20her%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20and%20filled%20out%20dozens%20of%20online%20applications%20and%20almost%20never%20heard%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20my%20age%2C%20I%20was%20just%20not%20attractive%20on%20paper%2C%20and%20not%20having%20a%20college%20degree%20was%20always%20a%20factor%2C%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20Crystal%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20could%20send%20out%20200%20applications%20and%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20and%20maybe%20get%20two%20calls%20and%20then%20not%20even%20be%20invited%20in%20for%20an%20interview.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Flifestyle%2Fcareers%2Femployers-open-more-doors-to-workers-without-degrees-but-few-are-getting-in-732f1098%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20US%20Census%20Bureau%20data%20from%202022%2C%2067.2%25%20of%20adults%2055%20and%20older%20do%20not%20have%20a%20bachelor's%20degree.%20While%20some%20jobs%2C%20like%20Walmart%2C%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fww