or%20%245%20where%20he%20doesn't%20quite%20break%20even.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20no%20government%20or%20public%20statistics%20from%20ride-hailing%20companies%20about%20the%20number%20of%20immigrants%20who%20drive.%20However%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Ffeatured-insights%2Fsustainable-inclusive-growth%2Ffuture-of-america%2Ffreelance-side-hustles-and-gigs-many-more-americans-have-become-independent-workers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enearly%20half%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20all%20immigrants%20reported%20being%20independent%20workers%2C%20according%20to%20a%20poll%20of%2025%2C062%20adults%20conducted%20by%20Ipsos%20on%20behalf%20of%20McKinsey%20and%20published%20in%20August%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimmigrant-owned-businesses-entrepreneurs-nyc-helping-communities-pandemic-2020-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimmigrants%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20gig%20work%20is%20the%20only%20income%20source%20they%20can%20find%2C%20said%20Katie%20Wells%2C%20a%20geographer%20at%20Georgetown%20University%20whose%20book%20%26quot%3BDisrupting%20DC%26quot%3B%20analyzes%20Uber's%20rise%20in%20the%20Washington%2C%20DC%20metro%20area.%20Many%20live%20a%20life%20of%20waiting%20%E2%80%94%20for%20their%20new%20lives%20to%20begin%2C%20for%20their%20remittances%20to%20transfer%2C%20and%20for%20their%20next%20passenger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20question%20of%20migration%20and%20the%20gig%20economy%20is%20not%20only%20showing%20up%20here%3B%20it%20is%20showing%20up%20across%20the%20world%20as%20sort%20of%20the%20new%20Ellis%20Island%2C%20so%20to%20speak%2C%20for%20migrant%20workers%2C%26quot%3B%20Wells%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20major%20ride-hailing%20companies%20told%20BI%20they%20aim%20to%20support%20immigrant%20drivers.%20In%20a%20statement%20to%20BI%2C%20an%20Uber%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20has%20a%20partnership%20with%20the%20language-learning%20platform%20Rosetta%20Sto