w.%20Most%2C%20though%2C%20outlined%20challenges%20such%20as%20not%20earning%20enough%20from%20driving%20amid%20heightened%20competition%2C%20the%20language%20barrier%2C%20not%20feeling%20adequately%20supported%20on%20their%20driver%20journeys%2C%20and%20feeling%20like%20they%20can't%20leave%20the%20platform%20due%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20other%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c9c878b0-179b-48b9-b18c-5fc11965c0db%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EImmigrants%20feel%20forced%20into%20gig%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20immigration%20has%20helped%20the%20US's%20economic%20rebound.%20According%20to%20an%20Economic%20Policy%20Institute%20analysis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2F2024%2F02%2F27%2Feconomy-immigration-border-biden%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecited%20by%20The%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20between%20January%202023%20and%20January%202024%2C%20about%2050%25%20of%20the%20labor%20market's%20growth%20was%20from%20foreign-born%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDozens%20of%20ride-hail%20drivers%20from%20across%20the%20country%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-driving-with-disability-low-earners-gig-work-flexibility-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espoke%20to%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20last%20few%20months%20said%20they've%20recently%20noticed%20more%20immigrant%20drivers%20on%20the%20apps.%20Some%20said%20they've%20seen%20immigrant%20drivers%20using%20fake%20accounts%20or%20borrowing%20existing%20accounts%20from%20other%20drivers%2C%20and%20some%20passengers%20have%20told%20them%20they've%20felt%20unsafe%20when%20the%20driver%20doesn't%20look%20like%20their%20profile%20picture%20on%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWells%20said%20many%20immigrants%20are%20attracted%20to%20driving%20platforms%20as%20they%20have%20a%20low%20barrier%20to%20entry%20with%20quick%20hiring.%20Drivers%20don't%20need%20strong%20English%20proficiency%3B%20they%20just%20need%20a%20driver's%20license%20and%20a%20car%20to%20start.%20While%20this%20allows%20many%20drivers%20to%20make%20money%2C%20there%20are%20inherent%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20risky%20for%20people%20that%20aren't%20understanding%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20work%2C%20understanding%20the%20risks%20to%20be%20out%20doing%20this%20type%20of%20work%2C%20but%20these%20platforms%20generally%20don't%20seem%20to%20care%20about%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Wells%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWells%20said%20that%20without%20large-scale%20data%2C%20it's%20impossible%20to%20know%20how%20much%20of%20this%20workforce%20consists%20of%20recent%20immigrants.%20She%20added%20that%20she's%20seen%20many%20immigrant%20communities%20unite%20and%20build%20solidarity%20around%20driving%20and%20delivery%20work%2C%20such%20as%20New%20York%20City's%20collective%20Los%20Deliveristas%20Unidos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2282c828d9-bdb5-4631-b5fc-3c9f8f5b5a50%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20hard%20for%20immigrants%20to%20find%20work%20outside%20ride-hailing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEdgar%2C%2060%2C%20ran%20an%20auto%20parts%20business%20in%20Venezuela%20that%20helped%20him%20stay%20afloat.%20But%20when%20he%20came%20to%20Miami%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20fleeing%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecountry's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvenezuela-economy-facts-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20collapse%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20quickly%20found%20that%20transferring%20his%20skills%20would%20be%20challenging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20first%20arrived%2C%20he%20didn't%20have%20the%20proper%20legal%20papers%20to%20find%20full-time%20employment%2C%20though%20that%20changed%20when%20Venezuelan%20immigrants%20were%20granted%20Temporary%20Protective%20Status.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20couldn't%20find%20managerial%20job%20openings%20and%20said%20his%20age%20has%20been%20a%20barrier%20to%20breaking%20into%20the%20industry.%20While%20he%20maintains%20his%20business%20in%20Venezuela%2C%20he's%20spent%20less%20time%20on%20it.%20Over%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20he%20applied%20to%20drive%20for%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20as%20a%20temporary%20solution%2C%20enjoying%20that%20he%20could%20be%20his%20own%20boss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNormally%2C%20people%20like%20me%20are%20retired%2C%20not%20working%20full-time%2C%26quot%3B%20Edgar%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20difficult%20to%20find%20a%20job%20with%20my%20skills.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20he's%20driven%2040%20to%2050%20hours%20a%20week%2C%20mostly%20Monday%20through%20Friday%2C%20while%20supporting%20three%20kids%20who%20are%20in%20college%20or%20the%20workforce.%20According%20to%20earnings%20statements%20viewed%20by%20BI%2C%20he%20makes%20%24700%20to%20%24800%20a%20week%2C%20which%20is%20reduced%20to%20%24400%20to%20%24500%20a%20week%20after%20gas%20and%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20my%20earnings%20are%20lower%20than%20before%20because%20Uber%20has%20been%20paying%20less%20per%20mile%20than%20last%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Edgar%20said.%20%26quot%3BRight%20now%2C%20there%20is%20great%20competition%20with%20this%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ED.%2C%20a%20Haitian%20immigrant%20who's%20driven%20for%20seven%20years%20and%20moved%20to%20the%20US%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20said%20he%20enjoys%20driving%20though%20it%20hasn't%20given%20him%20the%20level%20of%20financial%20security%20he's%20desired.%20He%20drives%20six%20days%20a%20week%20from%206%20a.m.%20until%204%20p.m.%3B%20on%20good%20days%2C%20he%20can%20pull%20in%20%24300%20to%20%24400%20before%20expenses%2C%20earnings%20statements%20confirm.%20He's%20had%20his%20fair%20share%20of%20rough%20driving%20days%20in%20Miami%20that%20have%20caused%20him%20stress%2C%20but%20he%20hasn't%20been%20able%20to%20find%20other%20types%20of%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20do%20it%20anyway%2C%20and%20if%20you%20don't%2C%20you%20won't%20have%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20just%20have%20to%20keep%20pushing%20and%20fighting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20same%20factors%20are%20at%20play%20for%20the%20children%20of%20immigrants.%20Alex%2C%2032%2C%20was%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20South%20Florida%20to%20parents%20who%20fled%20El%20Salvador.%20He%20was%20raised%20to%20work%20hard%20but%20wasn't%20given%20many%20opportunities%20to%20attend%20higher%20education%20or%20get%20an%20office%20job%2C%20given%20his%20English%20isn't%20perfect%20and%20his%20employment%20history%20isn't%20consistent%20with%20the%20demands%20of%20white-collar%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20provide%20for%20himself%20and%20his%20family%2C%20he%20started%20driving%20one%20to%20two%20days%20a%20week%20for%20Uber%20in%20February%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20working%20as%20an%20Amazon%20Flex%20driver.%20On%20average%2C%20he%20said%20he%20pulls%20in%20%24150%20a%20day%20for%20Uber%20after%20expenses.%20However%2C%20constant%20traffic%20has%20impeded%20his%20earnings.%20He%20said%20he%20makes%20more%20daily%20with%20Amazon%20Flex%2C%20which%20pays%20hourly%20and%20provides%20overtime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a3d027f6-3b22-494a-805f-e2999d8ea90b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20hard%20for%20immigrant%20drivers%20to%20find%20alternatives%2C%20but%20some%20make%20it%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20immigrants%20who%20spoke%20to%20BI%20said%20they've%20applied%20to%20all%20sorts%20of%20jobs%2C%20from%20maintenance%20and%20construction%20gigs%20to%20restaurants%20and%20retail%20positions%2C%20though%20they%20haven't%20had%20luck%20getting%20hired.%20Some%20say%20they%20suspect%20it's%20because%20of%20the%20language%20barrier%2C%20a%20lack%20of%20proper%20documentation%2C%20or%20limited%20employment%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20Eliezer%2C%20an%20Uber%20driver%20from%20Nicaragua%20with%20a%20nearly%205.0-star%20rating%20for%20two%20years%2C%20said%20he%20doesn't%20know%20if%20he'll%20be%20driving%20for%20much%20longer%2C%20although%20he%20hasn't%20had%20any%20leads%20on%20other%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20acknowledged%20that%20his%20earnings%20were%20not%20enough%20to%20live%20comfortably%2C%20but%20he%20didn't%20know%20what%20other%20jobs%20he%20could%20get%20with%20his%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20and%20work%20experience.%20He%20prioritizes%20driving%20around%20Miami%20Beach%2C%20and%20some%20weeks%2C%20he%20puts%20in%2070%20hours%20to%20make%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20driving%20for%20all%20my%20life%2C%20but%20this%20job%20permits%20me%20to%20travel%20to%20my%20country%20or%20other%20countries%20because%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20ask%20for%20permission%20when%20I%20want%20to%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20Eliezer%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20requesting%20time%20off%20from%20a%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20immigrants%20have%20successfully%20gotten%20other%20jobs%20and%20have%20relied%20on%20driving%20as%20supplemental%20income%2C%20leading%20some%20to%20live%20more%20comfortably.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarlos%2C%20who%20immigrated%20from%20Venezuela%2C%20drives%20part-time%20to%20supplement%20his%20real%20estate%20work%2C%20noting%20gig%20driving%20is%20an%20insufficient%20full-time%20job.%20While%20this%20year's%20spring%20break%20was%20much%20less%20crowded%20than%20in%20past%20years%2C%20which%20put%20a%20dent%20in%20his%20earnings%2C%20there%20weren't%20as%20many%20fights%20or%20security%20problems%20as%20in%20past%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicanor%2C%20who%20left%20Cuba%20in%201997%20and%20moved%20to%20New%20York%20before%20landing%20in%20Miami%2C%20drives%20for%20Uber%20a%20few%20days%20a%20month%20to%20supplement%20his%20full-time%20truck%20driving.%20He%20likes%20the%20part-time%20arrangement%2C%20which%20pulls%20in%20a%20few%20hundred%20dollars%20a%20month%2C%20allows%20him%20to%20focus%20on%20a%20job%20with%20more%20consistent%20earnings%2C%20and%20socialize.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20house%20and%20be%20alone%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20doesn't%20have%20much%20family%20in%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20challenges%20of%20earning%20enough%2C%20some%20drivers%20are%20set%20on%20perfecting%20strategies%20to%20make%20driving%20work%20for%20them.%20Especially%20since%20they've%20faced%20repeated%20disappointment%20getting%20hired%20in%20other%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Keylis%2C%20a%20young%20mother%20and%20recent%20immigrant%20from%20Cuba%2C%20driving%20for%20Uber%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bthe%20best%20thing%20that%20has%20happened%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20in%20Spanish.%20She%20worked%20another%20job%20when%20she%20first%20got%20to%20the%20US%20that%20wasn't%20as%20financially%20stable%2C%20plus%20she%20enjoys%20being%20her%20own%20boss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20makes%20about%20%241%2C200%20a%20week%20driving%20around%20downtown%20Miami%20after%20expenses%2C%20and%20she%20has%20little%20intention%20of%20stopping%20driving%20as%20her%20income%20is%20stable%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20she%20isn't%20sure%20she%20will%20have%20enough%20saved%20for%20a%20comfortable%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20gig%20driver%20who%20is%20struggling%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%3F%20Have%20you%20recently%20immigrated%20from%20a%20different%20country%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ansheidlower%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ensheidlower%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-florida-miami-fort-lauderdale-immigration-rideshare-driving-cuba-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715506021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6601c00916bde8d4ead