20proposed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20it%20wasn't%20a%20surprise.%20By%20the%20time%20I%20started%20wearing%20an%20engagement%20ring%2C%20we%20had%20already%20decided%20on%20what%20kind%20of%20wedding%20we%20wanted%20and%20where%20we%20would%20live.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20nearly%20up%20until%20my%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiggest-signs-a-marriage-will-work-or-not-wedding-expert-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewedding%20day%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20I%20couldn't%20decide%20whether%20I%20would%20change%20my%20last%20name.%20My%20husband%20was%20open%20that%20he%20wanted%20me%20to%20take%20his%20name%20of%20%26quot%3BSmith%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20assumed%20that%20I%20would%20keep%20my%20maiden%20name%20after%20we%20said%20our%20vows.%20I%20wasn't%20so%20sure.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2244ceeabc-ecb1-4688-9413-321ad8069b4f%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20didn't%20want%20to%20drop%20my%20maiden%20name%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20we%20got%20married%2C%20I%20was%2027.%20I%20had%20graduated%20from%20law%20school%20and%20started%20my%20career.%20I%20started%20building%20a%20reputation%20and%20spent%20hours%20networking%20with%20other%20attorneys.%20I%20was%20known%20by%20my%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchanged-last-name-husband-hyphenated-maiden-married-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emaiden%20name%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20professionally%20and%20didn't%20want%20to%20create%20any%20confusion%20that%20could%20derail%20my%20career%20track%20over%20a%20case%20of%20mistaken%20identity.%20Additionally%2C%20I%20had%20only%20had%20one%20name%20my%20entire%20life.%20My%20name%20was%20the%20thing%20in%20life%20I%20used%20the%20most%2C%20and%20it%20seemed%20odd%20to%20change%20it%20just%20because%20I%20was%20getting%20married.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20I%20very%20much%20wanted%20a%20family.%20I%20had%20heard%20from%20friends%20who%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchanged-kids-names-to-include-my-last-name-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enot%20changed%20their%20names%20to%20match%20their%20children's%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20it%20caused%20a%20lot%20of%20confusion.%20Teachers%20sometimes%20appeared%20unsure%20if%20they%20were%20their%20children's%20mother%20and%20it%20caused%20headaches%20when%20traveling.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-i-wish-i-knew-about-pregnancy-before-getting-pregnant-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20before%20becoming%20pregnant%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20wanted%20to%20share%20a%20common%20name%20with%20my%20children%20to%20make%20it%20clear%20to%20everyone%20that%20we%20belonged%20together%20and%20were%20a%20family.%20I%20ran%20the%20idea%20of%20giving%20our%20children%20my%20last%20name%20to%20my%20husband%2C%20but%20he%20also%20wanted%20his%20children%20to%20share%20his%20last%20name.%20I%20briefly%20asked%20my%20husband%20if%20he%20would%20ever%20consider%20changing%20his%20last%20name.%20He%20immediately%20said%20no%20and%20so%20the%20decision%20was%20left%20solely%20in%20my%20hands.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221d9bc71d-79f0-4c7e-bbb1-f6ff09f9ed24%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20added%20his%20last%20name%20to%20my%20name%20without%20dropping%20mine%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20my%20wedding%20date%20grew%20closer%2C%20I%20became%20more%20comfortable%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-didnt-change-my-last-name-after-marriage-how-its-going%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ename%20change%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20After%20all%2C%20my%20maiden%20name%2C%20%26quot%3BDavis%2C%26quot%3B%20was%20not%20a%20long-standing%20family%20identifier.%20While%20my%20husband's%20family%20had%20long%20borne%20the%20last%20name%20%26quot%3BSmith%2C%26quot%3B%20harkening%20back%20to%20a%20long-lost%20profession%20in%20Northern%20Europe%2C%20my%20family%20had%20a%20history%20of%20changing%20their%20last%20name.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20father%2C%20a%20first-generation%20American%20and%20the%20youngest%20of%20three%20was%20the%20first%20in%20his%20family%20to%20be%20given%20the%20last%20name%20Davis%20at%20birth.%20Before%20changing%20our%20family%20name%20to%20Davis%2C%20my%20Grandfather%20had%20changed%20his%20last%20name%20from%20Davidovitz%20to%20Davidovich%2C%20each%20time%20further%20obscuring%20his%20roots%20a%20little%20further.%20Many%20immigrants%20arriving%20in%20the%20US%20at%20that%20time%20adopted%20anglicized%20names%2C%20but%20for%20my%20Jewish%20family%2C%20it%20may%20have%20seemed%20essential%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Nazis%20were%20rising%20to%20power.%20Plus%2C%20my%20father's%20older%20sister%20thought%20Davidovich%20was%20too%20hard%20for%20her%20teachers%20to%20spell%20and%20for%20her%20friends%20to%20pronounce.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20family%20history%20made%20it%20easier%20to%20become%20comfortable%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20shedding%20my%20last%20name%20and%20adopting%20a%20new%20one.%20Still%2C%20Davis%20was%20the%20only%20last%20name%20I%20had%20ever%20had.%20Although%2C%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20it%20was%20a%20newly%20created%20family%20name%2C%20it%20was%20still%20mine%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20let%20it%20go%20completely.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20considered%20hyphenating%20my%20last%20name%2C%20which%20seemed%20cumbersome%2C%20and%20still%20wouldn't%20be%20the%20same%20last%20name%20as%20my%20husband%20and%20children.%20Eventually%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20use%20my%20maiden%20name%20as%20my%20middle%20name%2C%20a%20middle%20ground%20that%20would%20allow%20me%20to%20keep%20my%20old%20name%20and%20use%20a%20new%20one.%20We%20decided%20that%20we%20would%20give%20any%20sons%20we%20had%20the%20middle%20name%20of%20Davis%2C%20too%2C%20and%20our%20daughters'%20middle%20names%20would%20be%20the%20maiden%20names%20of%20our%20mothers.%20We%20would%20create%20a%20new%20family%20tradition.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20our%20wedding%2C%20I%20went%20to%20the%20Social%20Security%20office%20to%20make%20my%20new%20name%2C%20Jamie%20Davis%20Smith%2C%20official.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fd133a2c-e24a-4b4e-b7ea-e6063c4abb48%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPeople%20don't%20know%20what%20to%20call%20me%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20things%20didn't%20work%20out%20as%20planned.%20I%20started%20giving%20my%20name%20as%20Jamie%20Davis%20Smith%20everywhere.%20It%20caused%20mass%20confusion%20and%20continues%20to%20do%20so%20until%20this%20day.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhenever%20I%20make%20a%20reservation%2C%20I%20never%20know%20if%20I%20will%20be%20listed%20under%20Davis%20or%20Smith.%20Concerningly%2C%20I%20have%20medical%20records%20filed%20under%20the%20wrong%20last%20name%20and%20confused%20with%20someone%20else.%20Airlines%20have%20listed%20my%20last%20name%20incorrectly%2C%20causing%20problems%20when%20I%20go%20to%20check%20in%20with%20a%20ticket%20that%20doesn't%20match%20the%20way%20my%20name%20appears%20on%20my%20passport.%20I%20get%20called%20%26quot%3BMrs.%20Davis%26quot%3B%20frequently%2C%20and%20many%20people%20insert%20a%20hyphen%20between%20Davis%20and%20Smith%2C%20both%20of%20which%20frustrate%20me%20to%20no%20end.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%2C%20whenever%20I%20meet%20a%20woman%20getting%20married%2C%20I%20share%20that%20trying%20to%20have%20it%20both%20ways%20simply%20has%20not%20worked%20for%20me.%20If%20I%20could%20turn%20back%20time%2C%20I%20would%20choose%20another%20path.%20Perhaps%20I%20would%20hyp