y%2C%20via%20beautiful%20buildings%2C%20fighter%20pilots%20and%20statistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Second%20World%20War%2C%20Allied%20statisticians%20were%20applying%20their%20skills%20to%20minimising%20the%20number%20of%20bombers%20being%20shot%20down%20by%20the%20enemy%20fire.%20By%20studying%20the%20damage%20patterns%20of%20bombers%20returning%20from%20action%2C%20maps%20could%20be%20drawn%20up%20of%20the%20most%20frequently%20damaged%20parts%20of%20aeroplanes%20so%20that%20expensive%2C%20heavy%20armour%20could%20be%20added%20to%20these%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimple%20enough%2C%20right%3F%20Then%2C%20along%20comes%20statistician%20Abraham%20Wald%20who%20argues%20for%20the%20exact%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F2287454%3Forigin%3Dcrossref%5C%22%3Eopposite%20point%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20planes%20that%20they're%20studying%20are%20all%20those%20that%20did%20return%20from%20combat%20with%20extensive%20damage%2C%20but%20what%20about%20those%20that%20didn't%20return%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWald%20argues%20that%20armour%20should%20be%20added%20to%20those%20places%20that%20are%20undamaged%20on%20all%20the%20returning%20planes%2C%20as%20any%20plane%20hit%20in%20these%20undamaged%20areas%20was%20shot%20down%2C%20never%20making%20it%20back%20to%20be%20surveyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ESurvivorship%20bias%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20phenomenon%20is%20known%20as%20survivorship%20bias%2C%20or%20the%20cognitive%20and%20statistical%20bias%20introduced%20by%20only%20counting%20those%20that%20are%20around%20to%20count%20but%20ignoring%20those%20that%20haven't%20%E2%80%9Csurvived%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20take%20these%20examples%20to%20the%20absurd.%20Imagine%20a%20group%20of%20100%20people%2C%20all%20of%20whom%20have%20smoked%20their%20entire%20life.%20As%20a%20group%2C%20the%20smokers%20would%20die%20earlier%20of%20cancers%2C%20lung%20disease%20or%20heart%20disease%2C%20but%20one%20or%20two%20might%20defy%20the%20odds%20and%20live%20to%20100%20years%20of%20age.%20Now%20imagine%20the%20intrepid%20journalist%20interviewing%20the%20lucky%20soul%20on%20their%20100th%20birthday%20with%20that%20classic%20question%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20do%20you%20attribute%20your%20successful%20ageing%20to%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSmoking%20a%20pack%20a%20day%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%20newly%20minted%20centenarian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20seems%20obvious%20but%20survivorship%20bias%20is%20everywhere%20in%20society.%20We%20can%20all%20think%20of%20that%20one%20famous%20actor%20or%20entrepreneur%20who%20succeeded%20despite%20adversity%2C%20who%20worked%20hard%2C%20believed%20in%20themselves%20and%20one%20day%20made%20it.%20But%20we%20never%20read%20about%20or%20hear%20about%20the%20countless%20examples%20of%20people%20who%20tried%2C%20gave%20it%20their%20all%2C%20and%20never%20quite%20made%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20a%20good%20media%20story.%20But%20this%20creates%20a%20bias%2C%20we%20primarily%20hear%20the%20successes%2C%20never%20the%20failures.%20This%20bias%20applies%20to%20our%20perceptions%20of%20architecture%20(mostly%20great%20buildings%20from%20a%20given%20period%20%E2%80%9Csurvive%E2%80%9D)%2C%20to%20finances%20(we%20often%20hear%20examples%20of%20people%20who%20have%20succeeded%20in%20risky%20investments%2C%20those%20who%20fail%20don't%20sell%20books%20or%20self-help%20plans)%2C%20and%20to%20career%20plans%20(%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20work%20hard%2C%20and%20drop%20out%20of%20college%20now%2C%20you%20can%20be%20a%20successful%20athlete%20like%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20say%20those%20who%20have%20succeeded).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20work%20with%20a%20variety%20of%20older%20people%20and%20often%20include%20extreme%20outliers%20who%20have%20lived%20to%20extreme%20ages.%20We're%20currently%20studying%20over%2065-year-olds%20who%20have%20maintained%20unusually%20high%20levels%20of%20exercise%20into%20older%20age%20and%20have%20maintained%20excellent%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey're%20phenomenal%20examples%20of%20older%20humans%2C%20many%20of%20them%20are%20faster%2C%20fitter%2C%20and%20stronger%20than%20me%20by%20many%20of%20the%20measures%20we%20perform%20in%20the%20lab%2C%20despite%20being%20almost%20twice%20my%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20we%20know%20that%20their%20lifelong%20exercise%20is%20associated%20with%20their%20unusually%20good%20health%20into%20older%20age%2C%20we%20can't%20directly%20say%20one%20causes%20the%20other%20yet.%20It%20could%20be%20that%20highly%20active%20people%20are%20protected%20against%20chronic%20diseases%20such%20as%20cancers%2C%20diabetes%20and%20heart%20disease.%20But%20it%20also%20could%20be%20that%20these%20people%20are%20still%20active%20into%20older%20age%20as%20they've%20not%20been%20afflicted%20by%20cancers%2C%20diabetes%20or%20heart%20disease%20earlier%20in%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20there%20could%20be%20some%20unknown%20third%20factor%20that%20we've%20not%20yet%20identified%20about%20these%20people%20that%20both%20keeps%20them%20healthy%20and%20separately%20keeps%20them%20exercising.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20clarity%2C%20there%20are%20things%20that%20scientists%20like%20me%20will%20say%20in%20carefully%20caveated%2C%20scientific%20language%20that%20will%20probably%20help%20you%20to%20live%20longer.%20Being%20very%20physically%20active%2C%20not%20eating%20too%20much%20and%20not%20smoking%20are%20all%20on%20that%20list%2C%20along%20with%20generally%20having%20a%20positive%20outlook%20in%20life%2C%20and%20of%20course%2C%20picking%20the%20right%20parents%20and%20grandparents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECorrelation%20does%20not%20equal%20causation.%20That%20point%20is%20hammered%20home%20relentlessly%20to%20students%20in%20science%20degrees.%20It's%20how%20our%20brain%20works%2C%20we%20see%20a%20pattern%20between%20two%20variables%2C%20and%20assume%20they're%20linked%20in%20some%20way.%20But%20often%2C%20like%20in%20survivorship%20bias%2C%20we're%20not%20looking%20at%20all%20the%20data%2C%20and%20so%20finding%20patterns%20where%20there%20are%20none.%3Cimg%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F229159%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E(Author%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fbradley-elliott-1014864%5C%22%3EBradley%20Elliott%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20Senior%20Lecturer%20in%20Physiology%20at%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funiversity-of-westminster-916%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Westminster%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fwhy-you-should-never-take-nutrition-advice-from-a-centenarian-229159%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715491200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fcv10j9l_old-age_625x300_12_May_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwhy-you-shouldnt-take-nutrition-advice-from-people-whove-lived-over-100-years-5644546%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Its%20a%20cliche%20of%20reporting%20on%20people%20who%20reach%20100%20years%20of%20age%2C%20or%20even%20110%2C%20to%20ask%20them%20some%20variation%20of%20the%20question%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20did%20you%20do%20to%20live%20this%20long%3F%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%2